      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Politics of Oil, Then and Now</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Eugene I Gordon letter holds using our Strategic Petroleum Reserve when needed is good military and economic strategy</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Clinton Approves Releasing Some Oil From U.S. Reserve'' (front page, Sept. 23):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Clinton Approves Releasing Some Oil From U.S. Reserve'' (front page, Sept. 23):</p>
        <p>Using our Strategic Petroleum Reserve when needed is good military and economic strategy. A good economy is our best defense.</p>
        <p>An announcement by the president and presentation of a plan to be independent in 25 years would break the back of the oil problem and ultimately eliminate the need for costly Middle East involvement.</p>
        <p>EUGENE I. GORDON  Mountainside, N.J., Sept. 23, 2000</p>
      </block>
